"    Predictors of adverse outcome sickle cell disease",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 523px; height: 249px; background-image: url(data:image/gif;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    This graph shows the estimated probability of developing severe sickle cell disease (defined&nbsp;as death, stroke, frequent pain, or recurrant acute chest&nbsp;syndrome)&nbsp;by the age of 10 years (y-axis) according to the following factors: leukocyte count (x-axis); severe anemia (Hgb &lt;7 g/dL) during the second year of life, and dactylitis before the age of 1 year. In this cohort of patients, 3 percent were classified as being at high risk, 53 percent were classified as being at medium risk, and 44 percent were classified as being at low risk.",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"    </div>",
"    <div class=\"reference\">",
"     Data from Miller, ST, et al. Prediction of adverse outcomes in children with sickle cell disease. N Engl J Med 2000; 342:83.",
